tags: Doctor friendliness,Explanation of the health issue,Treatment satisfaction,Value for money,Wait time,
review:
* **** * ******** *** **** ********* ************* ******** ******** I am Punit Dubey, a high school teacher from DELHI UTTAM NAGAR. Many thanks to Dr. Abhishek Shekhar, his Assistants and team for making me feel comfortable and respectfully treated in your clinic. I came with the goal of being able to chew food properly again after many years of losing molars. To get a smile back was to be a bonus and we achieved all of that. I had researched implants thoroughly and I liked best, Dr. Abhishek Shekhar's procedure of single-piece basal implants (permanent teeth in 3 days). Implant procedure in India at the clinic in India was an affordable option for me. I had full mouth reconstruction followed with NexxZr zirconia bridge (metal free bridge) in India. For those thinking about this, I say to you, come prepared to make decisions. The 3 biggest ones to me were, deciding : style (shape), length and colour of teeth. Take a good look in the mirror to know your teeth. That will help you with decisions to make. Dr. Abhishek Shekhar is a perfectionist in his work. 
His treatment is 
1.Affordable
2.Easy on pocket 
3.Perfect with durability
4.Care and concern is top notch
I felt I received the best treatment possible.
Punit dubey

tags: Doctor friendliness,Explanation of the health issue,Treatment satisfaction,Value for money,
review:
Dr. Abhishek is very friendly having a serving attitude and explained very well about the pre and post treatment care. He gave different options for the choice of crown/bridge which is very appreciable. The bridge fitted perfectly on implants on the first attempt. I didn't have to consult him back after my treatment, so no side effects I have so far.  Even if I am Swede, I consider Dr. Abhishek as my Dentist furthermore.

Dr. Abhishek have been serious in taking care of me.  I highly recommend him to anyone who needs teeth care to consult with him. 

Sten Alsvall

review: Dr. Abhishek was the first dentist I came across who could diagnose and explain the issue with an expertise and honesty rare to find. After diagnosis, he guided us with the exact path and timeline to follow for the issue which has stayed with me for 5+ years. Since the issue was with my front tooth, it was going to be challenging; but I'm glad that worked out just fine. He could treat the issue from the very root within a month's time and I'm thankful for that. :)
